[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Now these are the commandments,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " statutes, and ordinances that the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God instructed me to teach you so that you may carry them out in the land where you are headed"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and that you may so revere the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God that you will keep all his statutes and commandments"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that I am giving"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you – you, your children, and your grandchildren – all your lives, to prolong your days. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Pay attention, Israel, and be careful to do this so that it may go well with you and that you may increase greatly in number"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – as the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", God of your ancestors,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said to you, you will have a land flowing with milk and honey."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Listen, Israel: The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is our God, the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " is one!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You must love"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God with your whole mind,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your whole being,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and all your strength."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " These words I am commanding you today must be kept in mind, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and you must teach"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " them to your children and speak of them as you sit in your house, as you walk along the road,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as you lie down, and as you get up. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You should tie them as a reminder on your forearm"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and fasten them as symbols"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " on your forehead. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Inscribe them on the doorframes of your houses and gates."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Then when the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God brings you to the land he promised your ancestors Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob to give you – a land with large, fine cities you did not build, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " houses filled with choice things you did not accumulate, hewn out cisterns you did not dig, and vineyards and olive groves you did not plant – and you eat your fill, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " be careful not to forget the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who brought you out of Egypt, that place of slavery."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You must revere the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God, serve him, and take oaths using only his name. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You must not go after other gods, those"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of the surrounding peoples, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " for the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God, who is present among you, is a jealous God and his anger will erupt against you and remove you from the land."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You must not put the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " your God to the test as you did at Massah."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Keep his"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " commandments very carefully,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as well as the stipulations and statutes he commanded you to observe. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Do whatever is proper"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and good before the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that it may go well with you and that you may enter and occupy the good land that he"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " promised your ancestors, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and that you may drive out all your enemies just as the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " said."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " When your children"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " ask you later on, “What are the stipulations, statutes, and ordinances that the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " our God commanded you?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " you must say to them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “We were Pharaoh’s slaves in Egypt, but the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " brought us out of Egypt in a powerful way."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And he"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " brought signs and great, devastating wonders on Egypt, on Pharaoh, and on his whole family"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " before our very eyes. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " He delivered us from there so that he could give us the land he had promised our ancestors. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " The "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " commanded us to obey all these statutes and to revere him"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " so that it may always go well for us and he may preserve us, as he has to this day. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " We will be innocent if we carefully keep all these commandments"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " before the "
  },
  {
    "type": "divine_name",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " our God, just as he demands.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]